.TH "ice_pkg_buf_alloc_section" 9 "ice_pkg_buf_alloc_section" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_pkg_buf_alloc_section \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" ice_pkg_buf_alloc_section
.BI "(struct ice_buf_build *bld "  ","
.BI "u32 type "  ","
.BI "u16 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bld" 12
pointer to pkg build (allocated by \fBice_pkg_buf_alloc\fP)
.IP "type" 12
the section type value
.IP "size" 12
the size of the section to reserve (in bytes)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reserves memory in the buffer for a section's content and updates the
buffers' status accordingly. This routine returns a pointer to the first
byte of the section start within the buffer, which is used to fill in the
section contents.
.SH "NOTE"
all package contents must be in Little Endian form.
